Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.71,0:00:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-[rapid hoofbeats]\N-[cart wheels rattling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.80,0:00:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.40,0:00:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[CAPTAIN] Are you sure, sir?\NThis is far enough?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.07,0:00:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[DENKEN] It will do.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.36,0:00:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I can make it\Nthe rest of the way by myself.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.49,0:00:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}This is where\Nour journey must end,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.87,0:00:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}for my journey\Ncontinues on foot.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.75,0:00:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If you're certain,\Ntravel safe, sir.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-[hoofbeats]\N-[cart wheels rattling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.38,0:00:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.40,0:01:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[♪ opening theme song playing]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.84,0:02:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's in ruins.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.09,0:02:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Well, it takes time to rebuild\Nafter a dragon attack.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.13,0:02:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I didn't realize{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.34,0:02:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}you guys had to deal\Nwith dragons up here.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.34,0:02:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The Plateau's fun never ends.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.81,0:03:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It could be much worse,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.10,0:03:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-you know.\N-How.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.64,0:03:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] When I traveled\Nwith Himmel and the others,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}we were attacked\Nby a thunder of dragons.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.36,0:03:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Can you even imagine\Nthat many in one place?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'd rather not.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.53,0:03:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Uh, just to clarify,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.07,0:03:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}do they not usually move\Nas a thunder?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Was this village attacked\Nby a thunder?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.24,0:03:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[MAYOR] Yes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Seems the beasts have made\Na nearby forest their home.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.20,0:03:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You three are our best shot\Nat defeating them.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.21,0:03:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}"Normal" around here\Nisn't very normal.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.58,0:03:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Not normal at all.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[men grunting]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Your village is\Npast the point of saving.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.86,0:03:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You should rebuild\Nsomewhere new.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.44,0:03:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}How could we?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.74,0:03:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}As dangerous as it is,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}this is our home.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-[MAN 1] Incoming.\N-[MAN 2] Let me help.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[MAN 3] Need more hands?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.00,0:04:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN]\NHe's right, Mistress Frieren.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.46,0:04:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That was a cruel thing to say.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.09,0:04:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Somebody's gotta\Nhelp these villagers.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.67,0:04:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}One dragon\Nis a challenge enough.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}To face a horde...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We will not come out unscathed.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.72,0:04:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We protect other people's homes,\Ndon't we?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It shall depend on the reward.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.73,0:04:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Alas, our village\Nis extremely poor.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.69,0:04:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I fear we have\Nnothing to pay you with.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.94,0:04:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You don't have\Na single grimoire?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}There's one,\Nbut it's terribly useless{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and I doubt\Nit's of any interest to you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.45,0:04:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It allows you to say\Ntongue twisters{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.24,0:04:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}without tripping\Nover your words.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.87,0:04:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] Goodness, that does sound\Nterribly useless.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.46,0:04:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At the end of the day,\Na spell is still a spell.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.55,0:04:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You mentioned\Nthey live in a nearby wood?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Yes, they're somewhere\Nin that forest up ahead.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If we can pick up\Neven a trace of mana,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.27,0:05:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}we can track them down.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.35,0:05:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.21,0:05:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NLooks like we continue straight.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.75,0:05:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm impressed\Nby your magic all the time.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.21,0:05:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But when it's\Nso applicable like this,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.67,0:05:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm reminded how amazing it is.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.80,0:05:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Do you have\Nany more praise for me?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You can't give in.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.05,0:05:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}No more careless praise.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.76,0:05:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's bad for Mistress Frieren's\Ndevelopment.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.23,0:05:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK]\NHm... I guess that's true.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] What exactly\Ndo you two take me for?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.90,0:05:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If anyone still cares,\Nthe dragons are this way.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.99,0:06:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-[FRIEREN] There they are.\N-[dragons snoring softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK]\NThat's a lot of dragons.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NBut luckily they're small.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They won't be nearly as strong\Nas that solar dragon.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.32,0:06:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Regardless of size,\Ndragons are smart.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.91,0:06:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Don't let them surround you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.28,0:06:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I say we draw them\Nto a single point{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.20,0:06:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and take them down at once.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.75,0:06:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Well, Stark?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.08,0:06:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Think that you're up\Nfor the job?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.25,0:06:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You're an experienced\Ndragon fighter these days.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.13,0:07:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Tall order.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.59,0:07:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}More like experienced bait.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.22,0:07:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[dragon growls]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.22,0:07:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Shall we begin?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.51,0:07:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You better actually fire\Nsome spells this time!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.64,0:07:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.23,0:07:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If you slay them all first,\NI won't have to.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.81,0:07:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark grunts]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.69,0:07:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[dragons growling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.74,0:07:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark grunting]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.46,0:07:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark gasps]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.55,0:07:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[dragon growling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.27,0:07:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark grunting]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.32,0:08:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark grunts]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.91,0:08:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Stark groans]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.47,0:08:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That job\Nwas ridiculously intense.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At least the village's church\Nwasn't destroyed.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Mr. Stark, I watched\Nan angry dragon{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}-chew on your head.\N-[dragon grunting]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.02,0:08:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] How are you\Nnot in worse shape?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Uh...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I got no clue.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.82,0:08:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Eisen's head\Nwas often chewed as well.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Durable skulls must be\Na normal warrior trait.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.07,0:08:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Mistress, nothing about\NMister Eisen is normal.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:08:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[MAYOR] It took some rummaging.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But here's\Nthe promised grimoire.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.54,0:09:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Thank you\Nfor protecting our village.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.85,0:09:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I've noticed an odd tendency.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.14,0:09:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Whenever we help someone out,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}you almost always\Nblindly demand payment.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.89,0:09:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Because Himmel the Hero\Ndid the same.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.15,0:09:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's surprising.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.52,0:09:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Agreed. I imagined him\Nas the sort that would want{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.86,0:09:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to help others for free.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.11,0:09:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Curious, huh?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.86,0:09:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Used to confound me, too.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.62,0:09:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Thank you so much\Nfor your help, sir.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.08,0:09:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[WOMAN] I only wish\Nthat there was some way{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.33,0:09:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}for us to properly repay you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.33,0:09:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But as you can see,\Nour village is poor.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.25,0:09:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Though we can't offer much,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.04,0:09:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I do hope you'll take this.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.17,0:09:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[EISEN]\NI won't allow it, Himmel.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We cannot accept their food.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:09:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Is that a grimoire?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.31,0:10:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[MAN] Uh, unfortunately not.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.02,0:10:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's a notebook we received\Nfrom a traveling merchant{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.44,0:10:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}some time ago.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.77,0:10:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We have no use for it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.69,0:10:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.74,0:10:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[scribbling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.53,0:10:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NI have a question, Himmel.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.95,0:10:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Why demand payment\Nin exchange for our aid,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.29,0:10:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}when you don't care\Nwhat we receive?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.92,0:10:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If they pay us,\Nthey don't owe us anything.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.29,0:10:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}No favors and no praise.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}After all, we are\Nthe party of heroes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.39,0:10:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We're meant to be\Nprotectors of the people,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.81,0:10:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}not collectors\Nof gratitude and debt.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.48,0:10:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We should give, not take.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.39,0:10:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.57,0:10:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If the people we help\Nare indebted to us,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.15,0:10:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}then the only people that we're\Ntruly serving are ourselves.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.03,0:10:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You see?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.20,0:11:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's why even\Nthe most ridiculous spells{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.33,0:11:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}suffice as payment in my eyes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.54,0:11:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Noble.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.54,0:11:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Now start thinking\Nof a good tongue twister.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.88,0:11:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] I still think\Nyou just want more grimoires.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.01,0:11:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] Next time,\Nmaybe you can ask for one{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.34,0:11:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}that prevents dragons\Nfrom biting your head.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.85,0:11:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.73,0:11:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[EISEN]\NWhat's your analysis, Frieren?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Is it letting up?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.77,0:11:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] It still looks like{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.02,0:11:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}we won't be able\Nto head out for a while.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.32,0:11:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[EISEN]\NThat's some terrible luck.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I can't believe\Nwe're stuck here.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.24,0:11:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'm so bored, I could die.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.49,0:11:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Blame the bottle ache,\Nnot the boredom.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.66,0:11:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Himmel chuckles]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.29,0:11:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.25,0:11:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Keep your spirits high,\Nmy brave friends!{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We're on\Na life-changing adventure{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.51,0:11:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to slay the Demon King.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.26,0:11:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[EISEN] Yet we haven't been\Nable to adventure for days now.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Adventures are about\Nmore than fighting{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.51,0:12:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and wandering pebbled roads.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.10,0:12:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Sometimes, an adventure\Ncan be enduring{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.06,0:12:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}a series\Nof dreadful days indoors.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.27,0:12:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[EISEN] Dreadful is your word,\Nnot ours.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Himmel gasps]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[EISEN] What are you\Nthrashing about for?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.36,0:12:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Has death come\Nto catch you, too?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HIMMEL] Uh...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.70,0:12:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[thunder rumbling]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[HIMMEL] It's nothing.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.79,0:12:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We've been waiting\Naround this city for a week{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and the weather still\Nhasn't gotten better.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.68,0:12:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Will you be able\Nto ferry us across today?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.56,0:12:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You must know the answer.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.81,0:12:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Though made of wood,\Nmy boat is not a coffin.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.61,0:13:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I suppose not.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I've heard of storms\Nover oceans,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.62,0:13:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}but I didn't know\Nthey can form over lakes, too.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Lake Korridor\Nis the largest body of water{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.08,0:13:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}in all the northern lands.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's larger than\Nsome inland seas.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.67,0:13:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] I believe it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.79,0:13:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You can hardly make out\Nthe far shore.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.13,0:13:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Immense mountain ranges{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.59,0:13:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to both the east and the west\Ndisrupt air currents,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.64,0:13:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}making this time of year\Nbrutally stormy.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's not uncommon\Nfor large, established ships{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.48,0:13:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to sink in this season.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.19,0:13:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN]\NAnd because of the wind,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.81,0:13:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}there's no chance we can cross\Nwith flying magic.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.23,0:13:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NIt would be difficult to fly{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.73,0:13:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to the other side\Non a clear day.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The distance to shore\Nis vaster than you think.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.16,0:13:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN]\NI might be able to make it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.58,0:13:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But skilled as you are,\Nyou lack the mana.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.62,0:13:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Perhaps we would be better off\Nventuring around the lake.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.91,0:13:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] We most certainly\Nwould not be.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.71,0:13:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Wait, why?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.29,0:13:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I told you about the mountains\Nto the east and the west.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.76,0:14:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[muffled] Mmm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They're as mighty as the lake.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.22,0:14:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Trying to barrel\Nour way through{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.64,0:14:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}without so much\Nas a mountain pass{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.22,0:14:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to hang our hats on...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.56,0:14:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[muffled] Mmm.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.06,0:14:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}...would be suicide.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.68,0:14:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We should stay put and wait\Nfor a few months.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.73,0:14:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It'll be leagues safer\Nand timelier{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.69,0:14:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}than challenging the elements\Nhead on with no plan.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.11,0:14:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Fortunately, this is\Na fairly large port city{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.70,0:14:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and trading hub.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.07,0:14:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's the perfect place\Nto pass the time.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.66,0:14:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.20,0:15:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] One winter later\Nand here we are.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Can you take us?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Yes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}But only if you're able to pay.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.29,0:15:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Even though\Nthe storms have passed,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.42,0:15:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}this voyage is not a safe one.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.30,0:15:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The risk will need to be\Nworth it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's almost offensive.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.30,0:15:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We'd have the funds if someone\Nhadn't bought so many grimoires.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.14,0:15:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Boredom took control.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Fine. If you can't pay,\Nwe'll exchange favors.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.31,0:15:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}On an island just offshore,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}there's an abandoned monastery.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.11,0:15:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's protected by a barrier.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.70,0:15:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}According to legend,\Nif you can get through,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}you'll find the memoirs\Nof Himmel the Hero.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.24,0:15:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}In my grandfather's time,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Himmel the Hero saved our city\Nand its people.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.71,0:16:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I've looked up to him\Never since I was a child.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.46,0:16:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We've been starving\Nfor those memoirs for ages.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.59,0:16:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I'd like you\Nto find them for me.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.72,0:16:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Himmel's memoirs, huh?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.05,0:16:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Poor Himmel.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.76,0:16:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}All that work to record\Nyour travels{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.85,0:16:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}just for the pages to slip away.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.97,0:16:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Must have been\Nvery disappointing.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.94,0:16:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I can't believe they've been\Nhiding there this whole while.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.74,0:16:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Sure.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You've got yourself\Na favor.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It feels like\Nwe're on the ocean.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.35,0:16:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Is that a whole fleet of ships?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.22,0:16:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Indeed.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.39,0:16:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}If you want to move people\Nor goods north,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.48,0:17:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}now is the best time to do it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.06,0:17:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}And the recent rumors\Nare playing a role.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.69,0:17:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}They say there's a Golden Land{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.28,0:17:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}where things from streets\Nto rooftops{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.07,0:17:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}are made of pure gold.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}More people are interested{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}in crossing the lake\Nthan normal.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A Golden Land?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.91,0:17:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You think it really exists?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.83,0:17:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[sailor chuckles] Who can say?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.71,0:17:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}All I know is\NI've never met anyone{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.67,0:17:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}who's actually been there.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.63,0:17:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Probably just another tall tale.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.59,0:17:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[SAILOR] There's the island.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.90,0:17:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I was expecting the barrier\Nto be much stronger.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.06,0:17:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}In its defense,\Nit must be several decades old.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.94,0:17:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I bet this monastery was nice.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.11,0:17:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Why would anybody abandon it?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.95,0:17:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A monster attacked{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.24,0:17:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}and the old roof couldn't\Nweather the damage.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.58,0:17:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}This place has been around\Nfor a long while.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.20,0:18:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That makes sense.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.66,0:18:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}And explains why they erected\Nthe barrier in a hurry.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.71,0:18:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Mm, and why was that?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.96,0:18:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Monasteries are known\Nto house books.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.46,0:18:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Especially ones that are old,\Nvaluable, and irreplaceable.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.93,0:18:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] So, uh...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.89,0:18:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN]\NSo they put up the barrier{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.60,0:18:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}to protect the books\Nthey couldn't take with them.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.64,0:18:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That should do it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.98,0:18:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Now, let's see what we can find.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN]\NWhat happened to the monks?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.61,0:18:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Where did they go?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.53,0:18:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[SAILOR] Who knows?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.99,0:18:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It was abandoned ages ago.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.28,0:18:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The only knowledge that remains\Nabout this place{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}is the legend\Nof Himmel the Hero's memoirs.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.62,0:18:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[footsteps]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.71,0:18:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[door creaks open]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[STARK] This library is massive.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.38,0:18:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] There's a statue\Nof Mr. Himmel.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.22,0:18:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}He nailed the pose\Nfor that one.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[Fern gasps softly]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.77,0:19:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.52,0:19:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Hello, book.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.27,0:19:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Is it you?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.82,0:19:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.74,0:19:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Yes.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.07,0:19:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}This is it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's Himmel's handwriting.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}♪{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.63,0:20:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FERN] What does it say?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.39,0:20:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}It's the tale\Nof a ridiculous journey.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.19,0:20:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Just everyday minutiae.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.31,0:20:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Here. I hope that you enjoy it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.19,0:20:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}At last, our fare\Nis paid in full.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.57,0:20:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I've heard plenty of stories\Nabout the elven mage{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.20,0:20:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}who traveled\Nwith the party of heroes,{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.66,0:20:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}but I never dreamed\NI'd meet her.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.50,0:20:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}So, what gave it away?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.67,0:20:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}The wistful look\Nthat came to your face{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.79,0:20:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}when you skimmed over the book.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.96,0:20:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}I can tell that\Nit's important to you.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.34,0:20:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}You should keep it.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.22,0:21:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}There are plenty\Nof other valuable books{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.30,0:21:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}tucked away in here.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.47,0:21:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}That's payment enough for me.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.98,0:21:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Did it actually\Nshow on my face?{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.64,0:21:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Only a little.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.86,0:21:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[SAILOR] Let's be off.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.15,0:21:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}We'll reach the far shore\Nbefore sunset.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.61,0:21:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}[FRIEREN] Mm...{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.91,0:21:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}A collection of catchphrases.\N[sighs]{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.41,0:21:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}My! What a waste\Nof good pages.{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.25,0:21:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Hang on, I wanna try!{\b0}
